        <docId>d06.txt</docId>
    </sentences>
    <sentences>
        <sentence>One may then apply ideas from calculus while working within the individual charts, since each chart lies within a linear space to which the usual rules of calculus apply. </sentence>
        <docId>d06.txt</docId>
    </sentences>
    <sentences>
        <sentence>If the charts are suitably compatible (namely, the transition from one chart to another is differentiable), then computations done in one chart are valid in any other differentiable chart.</sentence>
        <docId>d06.txt</docId>
